cs0x65.parkinglot.model

Class Ticket

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs0x65.parkinglot.model.Ticket

  • public class Ticket
extends Object
    The class represents a unique ticket or a parking session for a given car at an allocated parking slot. Additionally, each ticket is identified by the start and end times.
    If a car leaves the parking lot (by paying the due charges) and comes back again then a new ticket is created.

      • getDuration

        public long getDuration()
        Returns:
        the total duration of the parking session measured in milliseconds.

      • getDuration

        public long getDuration(ParkingLot.ParkedTimeUnit parkedTimeUnit)
        Parameters:
        parkedTimeUnit - ParkingLot.ParkedTimeUnit
        Returns:
        the total duration of the parking session measured in specified time unit and ceil'ed to nearest time unit.
        E.g. if the parkedTimeUnit is ParkingLot.ParkedTimeUnit.HOUR, and the duration is 9000 seconds i.e. 2.5 hours, then this method returns ceil'ed hours i.e. 3.
